members.name: _handleDialogCancelEvent
members.description:
Prevents the user from dismissing the dialog via the `cancel`
event (ESC key) when `isDismissible` is set to false.

members.name: _returnFocus
members.description:
Return focus to the specified element, providing the selector is valid
and the chosen element can be found.

members.name: renderCloseButton
members.description:
Template for the close button element. Called within the
main render function.

members.name: renderBackButton
members.description:
Template for the back button element. Called within the
main render function.

members.name: renderLeadingAction
members.description:
Render leadingAction button depending on prop availability.

1. If the prop `leadingAction` is not provided, the button is not rendered.
2. If the prop `leadingAction` is provided but any of the optional properties
are not provided, they fall back to their default values.

members.name: renderSupportingAction
members.description:
Render supportingAction button depending on prop availability.

1. If the prop `supportingAction` is not provided, the button is not rendered.
2. If the prop `supportingAction` is provided but any of the optional properties
are not provided, they fall back to their default values.
3. If `supportingAction` is provided but not `leadingAction`, log a warning and do
not render `supportingAction`.

members.name: renderModalContentAndFooter
members.description: Renders the modal inner content and footer of the modal.

members.name: _handleDialogLightDismiss
members.description: Dismisses the modal on backdrop click if `isDismissible` is `true`.

parameters.description: the click event targetting the modal/backdrop
parameters.name: event

members.name: _dispatchModalCustomEvent
members.description:
Note: We should aim to have a shareable event helper system to allow
us to share this across components in-future.

Dispatch a custom event.

To be used whenever we have behavioural events we want to
bubble up through the modal.

members.name: isRTL
members.description:
Returns true if the element is in Right to Left mode.
If a dir attribute is not explicitly set on the web component
then it falls back to the nearest parent with a dir attribute set.

A dir attribute being set will result in a reactive property.
If the component falls back to a parent dir attribute then the value
will not be reactive and is only computed once

You can only pass in either a leading or trailing label, if you pass both in
as true nothing renders.

declarations.name: requiredProperty
declarations.description:
A decorator for marking a property as required.
If the property's value is `undefined`, `null` or empty string, an error is logged.

declarations.description:
A decorator for specifying a list of valid values for a property.
If this property's setter is called with an invalid value, an error is logged and the default value will be assigned instead.
